"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-gretchen-walsh-swimming-short-course-world-championships-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Swimmer Gretchen Walsh is putting the finishing touches on what has been a record-breaking 2024 in three different sizes of pools.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8, \"end\": 22, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh, 21, earned her second individual gold medal in as many days at the world short course championships in Budapest, taking the 100m freestyle in the second-fastest time in history.\", \"from\": 132, \"to\": 316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 242, \"end\": 250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 0.9999999999590727, \"rank\": 4.094004710468909e-11, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later Thursday, American Jack Alexy won the men's 100m free for the first individual global title of his career.\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 334, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9856722678858851, \"rank\": 0.01417533361262937, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 343, \"end\": 347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.6386448596768338, \"rank\": 0.565024520787284, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. swept the men's and women's 100m free titles at short course worlds for the first time.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh clocked 50.31 seconds, just off the world record of 50.25 set by Australian Cate Campbell in 2017.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999453743566934, \"rank\": 3.157158830890849e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 611, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cate_Campbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cate Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cate_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cate_Campbell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SHORT COURSE WORLDS:Full Results|Broadcast Schedule  \\\"I pushed it in the first 50, went for it,\\\" said Walsh, who was 31 hundredths under world record pace at the halfway point.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's kind of what I do.\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Make it hurt, but I am really happy with that time.\\\"\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 100m free feat came a day after she won the 50m butterfly.\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In that event, Walsh recorded the three fastest times in history among her preliminary heat, semifinal and final swims on Tuesday and Wednesday.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Short course worlds are held in a 25-meter pool rather than the 50-meter pool used for the Olympics and other major international meets.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1238, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No matter, Walsh has excelled in all types of pools this year.\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It started in 25-yard pools used for NCAA competition.\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1341, \"end\": 1345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999119124862, \"rank\": 8.808757556142955e-08, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In February and March, she broke NCAA and American records across the 50- and 100-yard frees, 100 backstroke and 100 fly while swimming for the University of Virginia.\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1392, \"end\": 1396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999119124862, \"rank\": 8.808757556142955e-08, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\"}, {\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9856722678858851, \"rank\": 0.01417533361262937, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then at June's Olympic Trials, she broke the world record in the 100m fly in a 50-meter pool.\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She took silver in the event in Paris in her Olympic debut behind teammate Torri Huske, plus three more relay medals.\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1654, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999574260992, \"rank\": 4.2573752558850304e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1697, \"end\": 1708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh, the youngest 2016 Olympic Trials swimmer at age 13,was once labeled by some \\\"a bathtub swimmer,\\\"or somebody who has significantly better results in 25-yard NCAA pools than in 50-meter pools.\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1835, \"end\": 1842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.67014645421815e-15, \"text\": \"swimmer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999119124862, \"rank\": 8.808757556142955e-08, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_men's_swimming_and_diving_championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has transcended that limiting label.\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh's 2024 will go down in history.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Friday morning, she broke the short course world record in the 100m fly by 79 hundredths of a second.\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It does get hard, the pressure, but just managing it is definitely a skill to learn,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh became the first swimmer to break the world records in a 50-meter pool and a 25-meter pool and the American record in a 25-yard pool in the same individual event in one year since Ian Crocker in 2004 (also 100 fly), according to USA Swimming records.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2328, \"end\": 2336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9856722678858851, \"rank\": 0.01417533361262937, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2409, \"end\": 2420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Crocker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.964517233687006e-52, \"text\": \"Ian Crocker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Crocker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Crocker\"}, {\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh, Crocker, Rebecca Soni (2009), Kate Ziegler (2007) and Natalie Coughlin (2007) all broke individual records across the three pools in the same year if not confined to the same event.\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's possible more swimmers did as historical data is incomplete.\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ziegler deserves specific mention for breaking the world records in the 1500m freestyle in both pools and the American record in the equivalent 1650-yard freestyle in 2007.\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2737, \"end\": 2744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Ziegler\", \"score\": 0.9961064354750613, \"rank\": 0.003908177753119165, \"text\": \"Ziegler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Ziegler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Ziegler\"}, {\"begin\": 2847, \"end\": 2855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9856722678858851, \"rank\": 0.01417533361262937, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 1500-yard freestyle is not a recognized distance for record purposes.\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Also Thursday, Canadian Summer McIntosh earned her second world title and second world record of the week, taking the 200m butterfly in 1:59.32.\", \"from\": 2985, \"to\": 3129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3009, \"end\": 3024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Short course worlds continue with more finals Friday at 11:30 a.m.\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET, live onPeacock.\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3223, \"end\": 3233, \"title\": \"http://d